International Repair Day was established in 2017 to promote the value and importance of repairing, including at community events like [[w:Repair_café|Repair Cafés]] or [[Restart Parties]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/digital/elektroschrott-reparieren-ist-oekonomisch-und-oekologisch-sinnvoller-1.4176495|title="Reparieren ist ökonomisch und ökologisch sinnvoller"|last=Au|first=Interview von Caspar von|date=2018|work=sueddeutsche.de|access-date=2018-11-21|language=de|issn=0174-4917}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boingboing.net/2018/10/21/fix-stuff-better.html|title=Repair Day: How "contempt of business model" cheats you out of the use of your property / Boing Boing|website=boingboing.net|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-21}}</ref> The event occurs annually on the third Saturday in October. The first International Repair Day was organised on 21 October 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.voicemag.uk/blog/3325/dialogues-and-debates-ugo-vallauri|title=Dialogues and Debates: Ugo Vallauri|work=Voice Magazine|access-date=2018-11-21}}</ref> The second International Repair Day took place on 20 October 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boingboing.net/2018/10/21/fix-stuff-better.html|title=Repair Day: How "contempt of business model" cheats you out of the use of your property / Boing Boing|website=boingboing.net|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.positive.news/lifestyle/repair-fans-to-unite-for-annual-global-fix-fest/|title=Repair fans to unite for annual global fix fest - Positive News|date=2018-10-19|work=Positive News|access-date=2018-11-21|language=en-US}}</ref> The 2018 event focused on the [[w:Electronics_right_to_repair|Right to Repair]]: the right to access information and resources needed for repair, and the need for products to be more durable, efficient and repairable.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2018/10/its-repair-day-no-one-should-be-punished-contempt-business-model|title=It's Repair Day: No One Should Be Punished for "Contempt of Business Model"|last=Doctorow|first=Cory|date=2018-10-20|work=Electronic Frontier Foundation|access-date=2018-11-21|language=en}}</ref>
International Repair Day is organised by the Open Repair Alliance, an international group of repair organisations collaborating to make electronic products more durable and easier to repair, including The Repair Cafe Foundation (Netherlands), The Restart Project (UK), [[iFixit]], Anstiftung Foundation (Germany) and Fixit Clinic (United States).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://resource.co/article/international-repair-day-five-organisations-combating-throwaway-society-12910|title=International Repair Day: Five organisations combating the throwaway society|work=Resource Magazine|access-date=2018-11-21|language=en}}</ref> ==References== {{reflist}}
